The sentencing level of the system shall consist of at least the following information as relates to the sentence imposed:
Sentencing date;
Sentence for each offense;
If sentenced to imprisonment:
Place of imprisonment;
Sentence minimum for each offense;
Sentence maximum for each offense;
Consecutive multiple incarceration;
Concurrent multiple incarceration;
Was the defendant sentenced without privilege of parole for twenty-five (25) years; and
If answer to paragraph (f) of this subsection is yes, which aggravating circumstance or circumstances were found;
If sentenced to a fine:
The amount of the fine;
Is the fine to be paid in installments;
If answer to paragraph (b) of this subsection is yes, amount of each installment;
Was the fine paid in full upon conviction;
If not, what amount was paid; and
How much of money held for bail was used in payment of the fine;
If any other sentence was imposed:
The nature of the sentence;
Was conditional discharge imposed and what were the conditions of the discharge;
Was restitution imposed;
If restitution was imposed, what were the conditions of restitution;
If monetary restitution was imposed, what was the amount;
Was the amount paid in full upon conviction;
If restitution was to be paid in installments, what is the amount of each installment and to whom is it to be paid; and
List any other type of sentence imposed;
Were court costs imposed:
The amount of the costs;
Are the costs to be paid in installments;
If answer to paragraph (b) of this subsection is yes, the amount of each installment;
Were the costs paid in full upon conviction; and
If not, how much was paid;
Was a crime victim compensation fund cost imposed:
The amount imposed;
Is this amount to be paid in installments;
If answer to paragraph (b) of this subsection is yes, the amount of each installment;
Was the crime victim compensation fund cost paid in full upon conviction; and
If not, how much was paid;
List all other fees, costs, and similar monetary penalties which were imposed but not listed above:
List separately the amount of each;
List separately each to be paid in installments;
List separately the amount of each installment;
Were these costs paid in full upon conviction; list each; and
If not, list the amount paid on each.
